        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 16 at 12:36PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 1236 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Macomb Township, or near Romeo, moving northeast
at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Troy, St. Clair Shores, Mount Clemens, New Baltimore, Richmond,
Romeo, Sterling Heights, Clinton Township, Armada, Memphis, Macomb
Township, Roseville, Fraser, Utica, New Haven, Washington, Shelby
Township, Ray Center, Stoney Creek Metro Park, and Chesterfield
Township.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
